  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Atrial fibrillation (AF) is the most common arrhythmia in western countries and causes of up&#xD;
      to one quarter of ischemic strokes. The randomized eHealth-based Bavarian Alternative&#xD;
      Detection of Atrial Fibrillation study (eBRAVE-AF) tests the efficacy of an e-health based&#xD;
      strategy for the detection of AF. The e-health-based strategy consists of a smartphone-based&#xD;
      photophlethysmographic (PPG) screening and an ECG-based validation.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
